  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Backing Tracks\r\n\r\n**Define:** A record producer sent you the vocals for Something Just Like This and hired you to create a full backing track. The vocals are already included so your job is to add beats, bass, and leads that match the energy and timing.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Listen to the vocals and think about the mood and rhythm:\r\n\r\n- What kind of beat fits? Should the bass be smooth or punchy? Listen to the example below for inspiration.\r\n\r\n**Try:** Use beat, bass, and lead blocks to build your track.\r\n- Add loops so the code plays long enough to match the vocals. Adjust timing so everything lines up.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Listen to your song and make changes until it sounds right.\r\n\r\nTo finish this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- At least one beat, bass, and lead\r\n\r\n- Loops that cover the full length of the vocals",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
